data.text:
TOKIO, December 8 (A.AP.).-The Associated i

Press correspondent says that the U.S. has charged -'.

Lieut-General Masaharu Honuna, the conqueror of :

the Philippines, with permitting the death march of

Bataan and other atrocities against Filipinos and Ameri-

cans/ The indictment also names Lieut-Colonel Saicht ^

Ohta, commander of the military police in the Philip-

pines in 1942, Major Zanzo Saito, commander of "The

Tiger" unit of the Japanese army, Major Takashi

Tohei, commander, of the Kempeitai unit near Manila,

and Colonel Akira Nagahama, chief of the Kempetitai,

in the Philippines from late in 1942 tb 1945.
